10/03/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Education Minister Ecaterina Andronescu said Saturday (8 March) the government was close to finalising talks on a $60m loan from the World Bank for financing of rural education projects.
The government would co-finance the programme, which aims to improve teacher training, purchase modern equipment, and rebuild school buildings.
(Rompres, Mediafax - 10/03/03)
